    "recap_headline": "Mercer University",
    "recap_text": "COOKEVILLE\n, Tenn. \u2013 Despite racking up 12 hits and scoring 10 runs, the Mercer Bears (17-3) dropped their third loss of the season on Sunday afternoon to Tennessee Tech (8-12).\nDecisive Plays:\nBrant Baughcum\njumpstarted the scoring early in the first inning with a two-run home run (3). The Bears worked station-to-station the following frame to tack on four more runs. The Golden Eagles responded with a three-spot in the home half of the second to cut Mercer's advantage in half. A Jackson Rooker RBI single and a two-run double by Owen Lee tied the game, 6-6, in the third.\nTitan Kamaka\ncontinued his hot start to the season with a three-run homer (2) in the top of the fourth inning. Tennessee Tech scored eight runs in the home half of the frame headlined by three home runs.\nLogan Shepherd\nplated\nMichael Graziano\nwith an eighth-inning RBI double. Jorsixt Jimenez capped off the scoring with an RBI groundout in the home half of the frame.\nNotable Players:\nChris Katz\n:\n2-for-2, RBI, 2 R, 2 BB, HBP\nBrant Baughcum\n:\n2-for-4, 3 RBI, HR, 2 R, HBP\nTitan Kamaka\n:\n2-for-5, 4 RBI, HR, R\nNoteworthy:\nWith Sunday afternoon's loss to Tennessee Tech, the Mercer Bears have a 17-3 record through the first 20 games of the season. Mercer's 17 wins through the first 20 games of the season ties the best start to a season in Bears' history. The last time the Bears reached this mark was in 1969 under legendary Mercer head coach Claude D. Smith.\nNext Game:\nThe Bears conclude their five-game road trip with a midweek matchup against Florida A&M on Tuesday, March 17. First pitch is scheduled for 4:00 p.m. Pitching matchups are TBD. Live stats will be available\nhere\n."
